defaultGiven 
defaultthe limited Treaty basis of the EU in the field,
default as well as the broader fields of employment and 
defaultsocial inclusion,
default such activity respects the authority and autonomy of Member State sovereignty in the area, is legally non-binding, and therefore has no conse
defaultquences should a Member State
default decide not 
defaultto engage with EU developments. 
defaultThe European Commission therefore cannot refer a Member State to the ECJ for non-c
defaultompliance with this initiative, and the funds are designed to complement activities and national leve
defaultl. They are not designed replace national initiatives or to provide the Member States with a one-size-fits-all policy approach. It should also be noted that that relative to the problem, the amount of funds available is actually quite small.  
